WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:03.969
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.037 --> 00:05.705
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like ping pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.207
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.273 --> 00:08.608
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.675 --> 00:10.510
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.577 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.696
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.763 --> 00:30.697
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.637
{\an8}<i>[light upbeat music]</i>

00:37.704 --> 00:42.609
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:48.815 --> 00:51.918
<i>- Ever wonder what it's like</i>
<i>to grow up in a big family?</i>

00:51.985 --> 00:54.187
<i>Well, so does my teacher.</i>

00:54.254 --> 00:57.357
Our class assignment is to do
a report on our families.

00:57.424 --> 01:00.827
With ten sisters,
I can sum up mine in one word.

01:00.894 --> 01:02.429
<i>Chaos.</i>

01:02.495 --> 01:05.632
<i>It took 3 weeks,</i>
<i>4 boxes of pasta,</i>

01:05.698 --> 01:08.768
<i>2 tubes of glue,</i>
<i>and 27 popsicle sticks,</i>

01:08.835 --> 01:12.338
<i>but the centerpiece of</i>
<i>my project is finally finished.</i>

01:12.405 --> 01:15.475
<i>Pretty accurate representation</i>
<i>of the Loud family, I'd say,</i>

01:15.542 --> 01:17.777
but making this thing
was the easy part.

01:17.844 --> 01:20.480
The real challenge
is getting it to school on time

01:20.547 --> 01:22.615
and in one piece
to give my report.

01:22.682 --> 01:24.083
Sounds easy, right?

01:24.150 --> 01:25.385
Not in my house.

01:25.452 --> 01:27.187
If you want to get all ten
of your sisters

01:27.253 --> 01:28.788
out the door on time,

01:28.855 --> 01:32.125
you have to get up pretty early,
and you have to have a plan.

01:32.192 --> 01:37.664
<i>[loud thuds</i>
<i>and indistinct chatter]</i>

01:37.730 --> 01:40.467
The ten-headed beast has awoken.

01:40.533 --> 01:41.768
Wish me luck.

01:41.835 --> 01:42.836
<i>[cat yowls]</i>

01:42.902 --> 01:44.971
Ah!

01:45.038 --> 01:46.706
Not today, Luan.

01:46.773 --> 01:50.543
- Oh, we'll see about that.
"Pailure" is not an option.

01:50.610 --> 01:52.245
[laughs]
Get it?

01:52.312 --> 01:56.316
- I'll just take this to the car
later, but first, Luna.

01:56.382 --> 01:58.818
A little
"Man with the Plan" music?

01:58.885 --> 02:00.253
- You got it, man.

02:00.320 --> 02:01.855
[plays rock music]

02:01.921 --> 02:03.256
- It's my dollar!

02:03.323 --> 02:04.991
- No, it's mine!
- Let go!

02:05.058 --> 02:06.226
- No, you let go.
- Right on cue.

02:06.292 --> 02:07.660
- You let go!
- Stop it!

02:07.727 --> 02:09.127
both: Hey!

02:09.195 --> 02:10.797
[cash register bell rings]

02:10.864 --> 02:12.866
- Half for Lola.
Half for Lana.

02:12.932 --> 02:14.734
both: Thanks, Lincoln.

02:14.801 --> 02:16.736
- Good morning, Lincoln.
- Ah! Good morning, Lucy.

02:16.803 --> 02:19.472
{\an3}- For my new poem, I need a word
that rhymes with choose.

02:19.539 --> 02:22.008
- Uh, how about lose?
- That works.

02:22.075 --> 02:24.077
- Time to get dressed, Lily.

02:24.143 --> 02:25.912
{\an3}- Hey, Lincoln!
Think fast!

02:25.979 --> 02:27.747
[Lily giggles]
- [chuckles]

02:27.814 --> 02:29.015
{\an3}Nice catch,
Lincoln.

02:29.082 --> 02:31.784
- Nice throw, Lynn.
[Lily babbles]

02:31.851 --> 02:35.421
- O-M-G, Bobby, I literally had
to call you right away.

02:35.488 --> 02:38.124
I am just so excited
about the homecoming dance.

02:38.191 --> 02:41.728
I know, right?
You're so sweet.

02:41.794 --> 02:44.931
- I'll get the drop on you yet.
[laughs]

02:44.998 --> 02:47.233
Get it?
- What do you want?

02:47.300 --> 02:49.702
{\an1}- Lori, could you
maybe hang up the phone

02:49.769 --> 02:50.837
and get ready for school?

02:50.904 --> 02:52.338
- Cool it, twerp.

02:52.405 --> 02:54.741
{\an3}I'm quite capable
of doing two things at once.

02:54.807 --> 02:56.776
- [gasps]
- Leni?

02:56.843 --> 02:58.077
- Note to self.

02:58.144 --> 03:00.346
Never walk and chew gum
at the same time.

03:00.413 --> 03:02.882
- Time's running out.

03:02.949 --> 03:04.150
- Lincoln, think fast!

03:04.217 --> 03:08.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:08.655 --> 03:10.256
- Okay, let's get
you downstairs.

03:10.323 --> 03:12.825
- Scatter, she's gonna blow!
- Or not.

03:12.892 --> 03:13.960
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

03:14.027 --> 03:15.728
[Erlenmeyer flask whistles]

03:15.795 --> 03:18.698
[whistling stops]

03:18.765 --> 03:20.266
{\an1}Phew!

03:20.333 --> 03:22.535
{\an1}Lisa, you're always
forgetting the dinitrotoluene.

03:22.602 --> 03:25.705
{\an3}- Silly me.
Much appreciated.

03:25.772 --> 03:27.807
[explosion booms]

03:27.874 --> 03:29.375
I'm still alive!

03:29.442 --> 03:32.078
{\an1}- Ayeee!
Lucha libre!

03:32.145 --> 03:33.746
{\an3}[screams]

03:33.813 --> 03:36.549
[clatter and cat yowls]

03:36.616 --> 03:38.151
<i>Todo bien.</i>

03:38.217 --> 03:40.887
- Lily, pants.
[hamster chitters]

03:40.954 --> 03:42.388
[Lily babbles]

03:42.455 --> 03:44.223
- I was here first!
- No, I was!

03:44.290 --> 03:46.392
- Nuh-uh! I was!
- No way! I was!

03:46.459 --> 03:48.194
- You always say that!
- You do!

03:48.261 --> 03:49.696
both: Hey, no cutting!

03:53.833 --> 03:55.702
Thanks, Lincoln.

03:55.768 --> 03:58.771
♪ ♪

03:58.838 --> 04:00.306
- Has anyone seen my zit cream?

04:00.373 --> 04:02.709
- I literally found
the cutest dress to wear.

04:02.775 --> 04:04.410
- A word that rhymes with stuck.
- Luck.

04:04.477 --> 04:06.379
- How do you stop a rhino
from charging?

04:06.446 --> 04:08.281
- You take away his credit card.
- [laughs]

04:08.348 --> 04:10.249
- Mom said no solving
for X on the walls.

04:10.316 --> 04:12.619
Same. Blame.
Game. Fame.

04:12.685 --> 04:14.120
- Where the heck
are my roller skates?

04:14.187 --> 04:17.290
I've got field hockey today.

04:17.357 --> 04:19.926
{\an3}- Wait. There's no roller skates
in field hockey.

04:19.993 --> 04:22.262
- The way I play, there is.

04:22.328 --> 04:24.230
[Lily babbles]
- Gotcha.

04:24.297 --> 04:26.399
Phase one of Operation
Get Ready for School

04:26.466 --> 04:28.735
and Into the Car on Time
is complete.

04:28.801 --> 04:32.639
Now comes phase two,
breakfast.

04:32.705 --> 04:33.940
♪ ♪

04:34.007 --> 04:35.775
- Thank you!

04:39.045 --> 04:40.413
[sizzles]

04:40.480 --> 04:42.382
- Cooking is usually
Dad's territory,

04:42.448 --> 04:43.850
but I gave him
the day off

04:43.916 --> 04:46.219
'cause I have to kick things
into high gear.

04:46.285 --> 04:47.286
Egg whites for Leni.

04:47.353 --> 04:48.921
Sunny side up for Luna.

04:48.988 --> 04:50.390
Funny side up for Luan.

04:50.456 --> 04:51.624
- Great yolk.
[laughs]

04:51.691 --> 04:53.626
{\an1}- Scrambled for Lynn.
Fried for Lisa.

04:53.693 --> 04:55.328
{\an1}Deviled eggs for the twins,
and...

04:55.395 --> 04:57.063
{\an3}- Oh, and I picked out
the perfect tux for you to wear,

04:57.130 --> 04:58.898
Bobby.
- Hard-boiled for Lori.

04:58.965 --> 05:01.200
Extra goo-goo-gooey for Lily.

05:01.267 --> 05:02.268
- Goo goo goo.

05:02.335 --> 05:04.103
- And for Lucy,
extra well-done.

05:04.170 --> 05:07.607
{\an3}- If I had a heart,
it would be swelling right now.

05:09.542 --> 05:11.978
- All righty, then.
We are dressed and fed,

05:12.045 --> 05:13.946
and now we have our backpacks
and lunches

05:14.013 --> 05:15.982
prepared to dietary needs.

05:16.049 --> 05:19.152
We're just waiting on Lori.

05:19.218 --> 05:21.921
{\an1}- No, not puke, Bobby.
Puce.

05:21.988 --> 05:23.623
It's like a reddish brownish.
- [groans]

05:23.690 --> 05:25.958
Everyone, wait here
while I grab my project.

05:28.795 --> 05:32.999
Time for phase three, getting
you out the door in one piece.

05:33.066 --> 05:34.033
Whoa! Whoa!

05:34.100 --> 05:36.636
[grunting]
Whoa!

05:40.339 --> 05:43.409
Phew! Okay then,
we're all ready to go?

05:43.476 --> 05:45.845
{\an3}Time for phase four,
out the door.

05:45.912 --> 05:48.548
Like I said, if you want
to get all your sisters

05:48.614 --> 05:50.016
out the door on time,

05:50.083 --> 05:51.751
you have to have a plan.
- Fine.

05:51.818 --> 05:53.352
If you don't want
to wear the tux,

05:53.419 --> 05:54.887
then I don't want to go
to the dance!

05:54.954 --> 05:57.957
In fact, I don't even want
to go to school!

05:58.024 --> 05:59.225
{\an1}[screams]

05:59.292 --> 06:01.360
- So close.
Wait!

06:01.427 --> 06:04.297
[indistinct chatter]
No, no, no.

06:04.363 --> 06:06.332
Everyone, stay right
where you are.

06:06.399 --> 06:08.434
Lori, wait.

06:08.501 --> 06:10.269
You're the only one
who can drive us.

06:10.336 --> 06:12.371
- Get Mom to drive you!

06:12.438 --> 06:13.773
- But she's already left.

06:13.840 --> 06:16.342
- Ah! I'm blue!

06:16.409 --> 06:17.877
My skin's turned blue!

06:17.944 --> 06:20.847
{\an3}- Technically it's
a sallow shade of cerulean,

06:20.913 --> 06:22.081
but why split hairs?

06:22.148 --> 06:23.750
- Lisa, what did you do?

06:23.816 --> 06:25.752
- I secretly switched
Leni's blemish cream

06:25.818 --> 06:28.154
{\an3}for an experimental
skin pigmentation ointment

06:28.221 --> 06:29.155
I've been working on.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.890
- Why would you do that?

06:30.957 --> 06:33.059
- Because she wouldn't let me
try it on her if I had asked.

06:33.126 --> 06:35.895
- You go upstairs right now
and get something to fix it.

06:35.962 --> 06:39.665
{\an3}- Fine.
Hairless apes one, science zero.

06:39.732 --> 06:41.968
{\an3}- Can't something go my way
for once?

06:42.034 --> 06:44.237
{\an1}- You can't always get
what you want, bro.

06:44.303 --> 06:46.305
{\an3}- Lincoln,
I've finished my poem.

06:46.372 --> 06:47.907
It's called "Failure."

06:47.974 --> 06:50.009
{\an1}- Lucy, I really don't have time
for--

06:50.076 --> 06:51.177
{\an3}- Failure.

06:51.244 --> 06:52.311
It is not an option,

06:52.378 --> 06:53.913
yet it's something you choose.

06:53.980 --> 06:56.315
The man with the plan
is destined to lose.

06:56.382 --> 06:58.551
- Lily, where are your clothes?

06:58.618 --> 06:59.952
And where is your diaper?

07:00.019 --> 07:02.288
- Go poo-poo.
[laughs]

07:02.355 --> 07:03.856
[diaper squishes]

07:03.923 --> 07:06.259
- I found the diaper.

07:06.325 --> 07:09.996
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

07:10.062 --> 07:11.564
{\an1}- Failure.

07:11.631 --> 07:12.932
{\an1}You know there is no one else
to blame,

07:12.999 --> 07:16.569
{\an1}for the choices you make
are always the same.

07:16.636 --> 07:18.004
- Come on, Lori. Please?

07:18.070 --> 07:19.839
I have my report this morning.

07:19.906 --> 07:21.107
{\an1}<i>- Go away!</i>

07:21.174 --> 07:22.775
<i>- The peanut butter sandwich</i>
<i>is mine!</i>

07:22.842 --> 07:24.510
<i>- No, the jelly sandwich</i>
<i>is yours!</i>

07:24.577 --> 07:26.145
<i>- No!</i>
- Ugh!

07:26.212 --> 07:27.647
<i>- You like the peanut butter</i>
<i>and I like the jelly!</i>

07:27.713 --> 07:29.315
{\an1}- You like peanut butter
and I like jelly!

07:29.382 --> 07:30.883
- No, I like jelly and you--

07:30.950 --> 07:31.884
both: Hey!

07:31.951 --> 07:34.887
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:34.954 --> 07:38.925
{\an1}- Now you each have a peanut
butter and jelly sandwich.

07:38.991 --> 07:40.193
Now, get to the car.

07:40.259 --> 07:41.260
both: Thanks, Lincoln.

07:41.327 --> 07:42.328
- Here's the antidote.

07:42.395 --> 07:43.863
- Thank you.

07:43.930 --> 07:47.433
Wait a second.

07:47.500 --> 07:48.434
[bird chirps]

07:48.501 --> 07:50.703
The real antidote?

07:50.770 --> 07:54.440
{\an3}- Fine.
Hairless apes two, science zero.

07:54.507 --> 07:56.242
- Here.
- [gasps]

07:56.309 --> 07:57.677
{\an3}- Failure.

07:57.743 --> 07:59.612
{\an3}It's all your fault,
this streak of bad luck.

07:59.679 --> 08:02.281
{\an3}No escape from this cycle
in which you are stuck.

08:02.348 --> 08:03.382
{\an1}- Stop!

08:03.449 --> 08:05.151
I've got a poem for you now.

08:05.218 --> 08:06.252
It's called "Lucy."

08:06.319 --> 08:08.354
Dark as night, hair like tar.

08:08.421 --> 08:11.257
{\an1}Take your spooky self
to the car.

08:11.324 --> 08:12.892
{\an3}- Sigh.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.528
{\an3}Once again, your poetic
brilliance has put me to shame.

08:15.595 --> 08:17.763
- Think fast!
- Oh! Ow.

08:17.830 --> 08:19.498
- Where is my field hockey
stick?

08:19.565 --> 08:21.467
I have roller derby today.

08:21.534 --> 08:23.669
- There's no field hockey sticks
in roller derby.

08:23.736 --> 08:26.105
- The way I play, there is!

08:26.172 --> 08:28.174
Oh!

08:28.241 --> 08:29.442
- Finally.

08:29.508 --> 08:34.046
I look perfect and beautiful
again.

08:34.113 --> 08:35.715
- Oh, come on.

08:35.780 --> 08:38.351
I thought we were pails.
[laughs]

08:38.417 --> 08:40.352
Get it? Get it?

08:40.419 --> 08:43.155
- How am I gonna deal with Lori?

08:43.222 --> 08:45.157
Got it.

08:45.224 --> 08:46.292
<i>[phone line trilling]</i>

08:46.359 --> 08:47.560
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Hey, babe.

08:47.627 --> 08:48.895
It's your boyfriend, Bobby.

08:48.961 --> 08:50.963
I just wanted to say
that I'm sorry

08:51.030 --> 08:53.566
and that I will wear any tux
you want.

08:53.633 --> 08:56.302
<i>- [squeals]</i>
<i>Oh, Bobby!</i>

08:56.369 --> 08:57.770
<i>[laughs]</i>

08:57.837 --> 08:59.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:59.972 --> 09:01.307
{\an3}Would you hurry up,
Lincoln?

09:01.374 --> 09:02.775
It's always such a hassle

09:02.842 --> 09:05.111
{\an3}getting you out of the door
in the morning.

09:05.177 --> 09:09.448
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:11.317 --> 09:12.418
- What's all this?

09:12.485 --> 09:13.920
- It's my gear, dude.

09:13.986 --> 09:14.921
I have rehearsal.

09:14.987 --> 09:15.855
- And who is that?

09:15.922 --> 09:19.125
- This is my roadie, Chunk.

09:19.191 --> 09:20.126
- No, no, no.

09:20.192 --> 09:22.094
He was not part of the plan.

09:22.161 --> 09:23.396
{\an1}You, out.

09:23.462 --> 09:25.798
I'll take care of this.
- Thanks, bro.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.069
- [grunts]

09:31.470 --> 09:34.307
[grunts]

09:34.373 --> 09:36.742
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:36.809 --> 09:40.313
Operation complete,
and with ten minutes to spare.

09:40.379 --> 09:42.515
A Loud house first, I might add.

09:42.581 --> 09:44.183
Let's roll.

09:44.250 --> 09:45.351
[engine turns]

09:45.418 --> 09:48.120
[Luan laughs]

09:48.187 --> 09:49.622
Stop!

09:49.689 --> 09:50.856
[tires screech]

09:50.923 --> 09:54.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:54.226 --> 09:56.162
[sighs]

09:56.228 --> 09:59.699
Phew!
That was close.

09:59.765 --> 10:02.168
Aah!
[grunts]

10:04.704 --> 10:10.643
[in slow-motion]
No!

10:10.710 --> 10:14.814
[thud and clatter]

10:14.880 --> 10:17.750
All of this work
for nothing.

10:17.817 --> 10:19.452
How could I be so stupid?

10:19.518 --> 10:22.254
How? How? How?

10:22.321 --> 10:26.692
{\an3}- If you're done with your pity
party, maybe we could help?

10:26.759 --> 10:28.861
{\an3}- Yeah.
11 heads are better than 1.

10:28.928 --> 10:31.731
{\an1}- Try not to lose yours.
[laughs]

10:31.797 --> 10:34.600
{\an3}- Yeah, every little thing
is gonna be all right.

10:34.667 --> 10:36.736
- Really?
You'll help?

10:36.802 --> 10:38.804
both: It's what families do.

10:38.871 --> 10:41.707
- But I'm supposed to give
this report in ten minutes

10:41.774 --> 10:43.743
and this thing is destroyed.

10:43.809 --> 10:45.911
What can you guys do?

10:45.978 --> 10:49.615
In conclusion, in my family,
every day is a challenge,

10:49.682 --> 10:52.018
but you can be sure that
when I need them,

10:52.084 --> 10:55.121
my sisters will always
be there for me.

10:55.187 --> 10:57.256
All of them.

10:57.323 --> 11:01.093
And sure, life in the Loud house
can be summed up in one word.

11:01.160 --> 11:02.128
Chaos.

11:02.194 --> 11:03.763
But I love that chaos,

11:03.829 --> 11:06.565
and I wouldn't trade it
for the world.

11:06.632 --> 11:09.235
- That was a fantastic report,
Lincoln.

11:09.301 --> 11:10.870
I'm giving you an A.

11:10.936 --> 11:14.106
Ah!
- [gasps]

11:14.173 --> 11:16.542
- Make that an A-minus.

11:16.609 --> 11:18.144
{\an3}- Pailed it!
[laughs]

11:22.281 --> 11:25.217
{\an8}<i>[rock music]</i>

11:25.284 --> 11:30.222
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.289 --> 11:32.725
<i>- And finally,</i>
<i>the motion to ration shampoo</i>

11:32.792 --> 11:35.227
due to chronic shortages
passed...

11:35.294 --> 11:36.896
by a hair!

11:36.962 --> 11:38.564
[laughs]
[all groan]

11:38.631 --> 11:42.134
{\an1}- So the minutes from our last
meeting are approved.

11:42.201 --> 11:44.070
Any new business?

11:44.136 --> 11:47.273
Anyone?
Anyone?

11:47.339 --> 11:48.607
No one?
- Lori!

11:48.674 --> 11:50.109
- I'm just messing with you.

11:50.176 --> 11:52.211
Lincoln has the floor.

11:52.278 --> 11:53.712
{\an3}- As you all know,
our annual trip

11:53.779 --> 11:56.348
to Scratchy Bottom Campgrounds
is quickly approaching.

11:56.415 --> 11:57.516
[all groan]

11:57.583 --> 11:59.385
- That place is the worst.

11:59.452 --> 12:01.220
Bears always steal our food.

12:01.287 --> 12:02.588
- [roars]

12:02.655 --> 12:04.957
- And we have to sleep
on the hard ground.

12:05.024 --> 12:06.525
- And poop in the woods.

12:06.592 --> 12:08.094
- I like pooping in the woods.

12:08.160 --> 12:11.964
- And the Dipterum Culicidae are
the size of Mustelas Nivalis.

12:12.031 --> 12:13.732
[crickets chirping]

12:13.799 --> 12:16.635
The mosquitoes are the size
of weasels.

12:16.702 --> 12:19.672
- And don't forget the scary
hill people hiding in the trees.

12:19.738 --> 12:22.241
- There's no such thing
as hill people, Lincoln.

12:22.308 --> 12:23.843
- My point is,

12:23.909 --> 12:27.179
why can't we go someplace
different like Aloha Beach

12:27.246 --> 12:29.348
or Dairyland Amusement Park?

12:29.415 --> 12:31.884
- Because Mom and Dad
will never go for it.

12:31.951 --> 12:34.186
- How do we know?
We've never asked.

12:34.253 --> 12:36.789
[overlapping chatter]

12:36.856 --> 12:38.324
- Fine.

12:38.390 --> 12:42.128
All in favor of Lincoln wasting
his time and asking Mom and Dad?

12:42.194 --> 12:44.463
{\an1}[sighs]
Motion passes.

12:44.530 --> 12:46.499
- Fine with us, sweetie.
- Sure, son.

12:46.565 --> 12:47.967
I don't see why not.

12:48.033 --> 12:50.136
[all cheering]

12:50.202 --> 12:51.470
- So which is it?

12:51.537 --> 12:53.172
Aloha Beach or Dairyland?

12:53.239 --> 12:54.874
- Oh, they didn't say.

12:54.940 --> 12:57.042
{\an3}I guess it's up to us
to decide.

12:57.109 --> 12:59.311
All in favor of Aloha Beach?

12:59.378 --> 13:00.646
One, two, three, four, five.

13:00.713 --> 13:02.815
{\an3}- You want to go to the beach,
Lucy?

13:02.882 --> 13:03.883
- Two words.

13:03.949 --> 13:05.351
Shark attacks.

13:05.417 --> 13:07.119
- All in favor of Dairyland?

13:07.186 --> 13:08.487
One, two, three, four, five.

13:08.554 --> 13:11.357
- It's five against five.
We win!

13:11.423 --> 13:12.858
- It's a tie, Leni.

13:12.925 --> 13:14.193
- Wait a minute.

13:14.260 --> 13:15.594
Lincoln didn't vote.

13:15.661 --> 13:17.596
{\an1}- Well, Lincoln,
what's it gonna be?

13:17.663 --> 13:19.365
- It's so hard to choose.

13:19.431 --> 13:21.233
I really like the beach...

13:21.300 --> 13:23.502
[overlapping chatter]

13:23.569 --> 13:25.538
But I love Dairyland.

13:25.604 --> 13:28.741
[overlapping chatter]

13:28.807 --> 13:30.509
I don't know.
I can't decide.

13:30.576 --> 13:31.777
I need more time.

13:31.844 --> 13:33.179
Can I have till the end
of the day?

13:33.245 --> 13:34.980
- Really?
- Fine.

13:35.047 --> 13:37.883
You have until the end
of the day to decide.

13:37.950 --> 13:38.918
[bangs table]

13:38.984 --> 13:40.419
- [sighs]

13:40.486 --> 13:41.720
Now I've done it.

13:41.787 --> 13:44.056
If I choose Aloha Beach,
five of my sisters

13:44.123 --> 13:45.691
are gonna be mad at me,

13:45.758 --> 13:48.260
and if I choose Dairyland,
the other five will be mad.

13:48.327 --> 13:50.062
Making a decision
is gonna be rough.

13:50.129 --> 13:52.097
- Hey, Linky.

13:52.164 --> 13:54.300
I brought you something.

13:54.366 --> 13:57.169
{\an1}A short stack
from your favorite short stack.

13:57.236 --> 14:00.739
{\an1}You should never make a big
decision on an empty stomach.

14:00.806 --> 14:03.375
{\an3}- Wow.
Thanks, Lola.

14:03.442 --> 14:04.877
- Hey, little bro.

14:04.944 --> 14:07.246
I was just thinking,
with all the pressure

14:07.313 --> 14:09.281
you're under to decide,

14:09.348 --> 14:12.184
{\an1}maybe a massage
would help you relax.

14:12.251 --> 14:14.720
Hiya!

14:14.787 --> 14:18.891
- [voice shaking]
Uh, this is awkward.

14:18.958 --> 14:20.226
Down a little.

14:20.292 --> 14:24.663
I carry most of my stress
in my lower back.

14:24.730 --> 14:26.065
Ahh.

14:27.733 --> 14:29.268
- Shower time.
- Huh?

14:29.335 --> 14:31.570
- Take a nice long one.

14:31.637 --> 14:33.872
I cleared the bathroom schedule.
- Wait.

14:33.939 --> 14:35.474
{\an1}You guys aren't trying
to get my vote

14:35.541 --> 14:37.776
{\an1}for Aloha Beach,
are you?

14:37.843 --> 14:39.011
both: No.
- No, no, no.

14:39.078 --> 14:40.346
- Wait, I thought we were.

14:40.412 --> 14:42.147
[sighing together]

14:42.214 --> 14:44.149
<i>[mechanical whirring]</i>

14:45.317 --> 14:46.585
- Cleaning my room?

14:46.652 --> 14:48.153
You guys aren't trying
to get my vote

14:48.220 --> 14:50.122
for Dairyland, are you?

14:50.189 --> 14:51.590
- What? No.
- No, no.

14:51.657 --> 14:55.194
- Now that's funny.
- Of course we are.

14:55.261 --> 14:56.996
- I amend my earlier statement.

14:57.062 --> 14:59.198
Deciding on where to go
for our vacation

14:59.265 --> 15:02.601
might not be so rough after all.

15:02.668 --> 15:05.504
all: Aloha, Lincoln.

15:05.571 --> 15:09.174
[light Hawaiian music]

15:09.241 --> 15:11.377
- What's that?
- It's your homework.

15:11.443 --> 15:12.444
{\an3}All done.

15:12.511 --> 15:14.380
- Uh, you did it?

15:14.446 --> 15:16.282
- I did.
- Phew!

15:16.348 --> 15:18.584
I mean, not that it matters.

15:18.651 --> 15:19.918
[clown horn honks]
[gasps]

15:19.985 --> 15:22.288
- Hiya, Lincoln!

15:22.354 --> 15:24.056
- Tippy the cow!

15:24.123 --> 15:25.491
- Well, that's right!

15:25.557 --> 15:29.695
And guess what I have
for my favorite fan!

15:29.762 --> 15:31.964
{\an3}- You did my laundry?
Wow.

15:32.031 --> 15:32.965
Thanks, Tippy.

15:33.032 --> 15:34.233
- You're welcome.

15:34.300 --> 15:36.001
[clown horn honks]
I'll see you soon

15:36.068 --> 15:42.141
{\an1}at America's favorite
dairy-themed a-moo-sement park!

15:42.207 --> 15:44.076
- Bye, Tippy!

15:44.143 --> 15:46.245
I love that cow.

15:46.312 --> 15:49.548
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:49.615 --> 15:51.917
- Welcome to your own
private beach

15:51.984 --> 15:56.622
where we have sun, sand,
and surf.

15:58.324 --> 16:00.292
- Don't forget screams.

16:00.359 --> 16:01.593
[girls gasp]
- [roars]

16:01.660 --> 16:02.795
[girls scream]

16:02.861 --> 16:04.029
- And if you vote Team Beach,

16:04.096 --> 16:06.398
the fun
will literally never stop.

16:06.465 --> 16:09.802
{\an3}- Yeah. If you need anything
else, just give us a toot.

16:09.868 --> 16:11.970
[blows note on conch shell]

16:12.037 --> 16:13.706
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:16.709 --> 16:17.876
- What's happening?

16:17.943 --> 16:19.945
- All aboard the I-Screamer!

16:20.012 --> 16:24.450
- Please keep your arms and legs
inside the ride at all times.

16:24.516 --> 16:25.617
- Woo-hoo!

16:25.684 --> 16:28.220
Faster, faster!

16:28.287 --> 16:29.688
[laughs]

16:29.755 --> 16:31.623
- Hope you enjoyed
the ride, bro.

16:31.690 --> 16:33.425
- If you vote for Dairyland,

16:33.492 --> 16:37.529
{\an1}you'll have 2% more fun.
[laughs]

16:37.596 --> 16:39.765
- If you require our services...
[rings cowbell]

16:39.832 --> 16:41.800
Just call on Team Tippy.

16:41.867 --> 16:45.904
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

16:45.971 --> 16:46.939
[rings cowbell]

16:47.005 --> 16:50.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:51.009 --> 16:52.611
[blows note on conch shell]

16:52.678 --> 16:55.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:55.447 --> 16:56.382
[rings cowbell]

16:56.448 --> 16:58.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:58.450 --> 16:59.418
[blows note on conch shell]

16:59.485 --> 17:02.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:02.221 --> 17:03.155
[rings cowbell]

17:03.222 --> 17:06.558
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:06.625 --> 17:07.593
[blows note on conch shell]

17:07.659 --> 17:09.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:09.094 --> 17:10.028
[rings cowbell]

17:10.095 --> 17:12.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:12.330 --> 17:13.565
- All right, Lincoln.

17:13.632 --> 17:14.767
Your time's up.

17:14.833 --> 17:16.435
What's it gonna be?

17:16.502 --> 17:19.238
- I know I said I'd decide
by the end of the day,

17:19.304 --> 17:21.406
but I'm still torn.

17:21.473 --> 17:23.809
Can I have just one more day?

17:23.876 --> 17:26.377
- Why, you lousy little--

17:26.444 --> 17:29.481
{\an1}- Uh, not a problem.
[chuckles]

17:29.548 --> 17:31.150
We understand.

17:31.216 --> 17:33.652
- All right.
- For sure, Lincoln.

17:33.719 --> 17:34.820
- Can you blame me?

17:34.887 --> 17:36.188
No matter what I decide,

17:36.255 --> 17:38.390
five of them are still gonna
be mad at me,

17:38.457 --> 17:41.226
but this day has been amazing.

17:41.293 --> 17:45.097
So I figure why not take
advantage of it a little longer?

17:45.164 --> 17:47.800
<i>- Ugh! What are we going to do,</i>
<i>you guys?</i>

17:47.866 --> 17:51.003
We need to try harder to show
him why the beach is better.

17:51.069 --> 17:56.809
- Or maybe we show him
why Dairyland is worse.

17:59.144 --> 18:01.580
- Got to pee, got to pee,
got to pee!

18:01.647 --> 18:03.315
Note to self.
No more cocoa before bed.

18:03.382 --> 18:04.616
What's going on?

18:04.683 --> 18:06.218
- Waiting in line
for the bathroom.

18:06.285 --> 18:07.686
Better get used
to standing in lines

18:07.753 --> 18:09.955
if you're gonna vote
for Dairyland.

18:10.022 --> 18:12.758
- [yelping]
- [yawns]

18:12.825 --> 18:14.259
[toilet flushes]

18:14.326 --> 18:16.528
Ah! Ooh! Ah!

18:16.595 --> 18:17.996
Aah!

18:18.063 --> 18:19.164
{\an1}<i>What?</i>

18:19.231 --> 18:22.601
{\an1}"Sorry! This ride
is temporarily closed"?

18:22.668 --> 18:24.937
{\an1}<i>No!</i>

18:25.003 --> 18:28.774
- Oh, so that's
how they want to play?

18:28.841 --> 18:30.776
- [whimpers]

18:30.843 --> 18:34.546
[water running]
Ahh, sweet relief!

18:34.613 --> 18:36.949
Ah! Freezing!

18:37.015 --> 18:39.117
{\an1}What happened
to all the hot water?

18:39.184 --> 18:41.653
- You better get used to it
if you vote for the beach.

18:41.720 --> 18:44.223
- Because the average ocean
temperature

18:44.289 --> 18:46.992
is 16.6 degrees Celsius.

18:55.868 --> 18:57.669
- Uh, guys, FYI,

18:57.736 --> 19:01.673
sand in my crack does not make
me want to vote for the beach.

19:01.740 --> 19:03.141
[both laugh]

19:05.511 --> 19:07.379
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:07.446 --> 19:08.947
Guys! Guys, too fast!

19:09.014 --> 19:10.816
Too fast, guys!
Guys, too fast!

19:10.883 --> 19:13.785
I'm gonna hurl!
[vomits]

19:16.154 --> 19:17.623
Word of advice.

19:17.689 --> 19:21.026
Blowing chunks does not make me
want to vote for Dairyland.

19:23.462 --> 19:25.764
"Everything you'll need for fun
in the sun.

19:25.831 --> 19:29.434
Enjoy. Team Beach."

19:29.501 --> 19:31.503
SPF 800 sunscreen.

19:31.570 --> 19:35.140
Perfect for my fair skin.

19:35.207 --> 19:36.608
Hm, tingly.

19:36.675 --> 19:38.176
[skin sizzles]

19:38.243 --> 19:41.880
[bell rings]
Aah! News flash!

19:41.947 --> 19:44.683
{\an1}Giving me a sunburn
is not the way to win my vote.

19:44.750 --> 19:48.320
- Huh?
Sodium hydrochlorite?

19:48.387 --> 19:49.888
"Avoid contact with skin"?

19:49.955 --> 19:52.758
{\an1}This has Lisa written
all over it.

19:52.824 --> 19:56.695
- So that's how you spell Lisa?

19:56.762 --> 19:58.063
[clown horn honks]
- [gasps]

19:58.130 --> 20:00.232
{\an1}Tippy!
Ah!

20:00.299 --> 20:01.633
{\an1}Mad cow!
Mad cow!

20:01.700 --> 20:03.101
<i>[screaming]</i>

20:03.168 --> 20:04.803
<i>[grunting]</i>

20:06.371 --> 20:07.406
[sighs]

20:07.472 --> 20:08.674
{\an1}- Well?

20:08.740 --> 20:10.075
- Worked like a charm.

20:10.142 --> 20:11.877
Aloha Beach is in our future.

20:11.944 --> 20:13.512
- We knew it!

20:13.579 --> 20:15.847
You've been sabotaging us.

20:15.914 --> 20:17.749
- We sabotaged you?

20:17.816 --> 20:20.018
{\an1}You put sand
in Lincoln's underpants.

20:20.085 --> 20:22.721
{\an3}- But you started it
with the line for the bathroom.

20:22.788 --> 20:25.591
[overlapping arguing]

20:25.657 --> 20:26.925
- [groans]

20:26.992 --> 20:29.528
[rings cowbell and blows conch]

20:29.595 --> 20:31.430
<i>Can I get an ice pack?</i>

20:31.496 --> 20:33.432
<i>Some bandages?</i>

20:33.498 --> 20:34.833
<i>A hug?</i>

20:34.900 --> 20:36.602
Where is everybody?

20:36.668 --> 20:38.036
[overlapping arguing]

20:38.103 --> 20:39.504
<i>[rings cowbell and blows conch]</i>

20:39.571 --> 20:40.939
I'm blowing the conch,

20:41.006 --> 20:43.275
{\an3}I'm ringing the bell,
and yet, nothing.

20:43.342 --> 20:44.276
- You!

20:44.343 --> 20:46.945
This is all your fault.
- Yeah.

20:47.012 --> 20:48.880
If you had just made up
your mind,

20:48.947 --> 20:50.649
none of this
would have happened.

20:50.716 --> 20:52.884
[overlapping arguing]

20:52.951 --> 20:54.686
- Great.
I was afraid of making

20:54.753 --> 20:56.488
five of my sisters mad at me,

20:56.555 --> 20:58.223
but now all ten are.

20:58.290 --> 21:00.225
There's only one thing
left to do.

21:00.292 --> 21:02.294
- Fine with us, sweetie.
- Sure, son.

21:02.361 --> 21:03.662
I don't see why not.

21:03.729 --> 21:05.497
- Quiet down!

21:05.564 --> 21:07.065
I've made my decision.

21:07.132 --> 21:10.836
We're going
to Scratchy Bottom Campgrounds!

21:10.902 --> 21:13.205
all: What?
- But what about the bears?

21:13.271 --> 21:15.707
- And the Dipterum Culicidae
bites?

21:15.774 --> 21:17.209
{\an1}- And the pooping
in the woods?

21:17.275 --> 21:19.611
{\an3}- That's still the only reason
I'd go.

21:19.678 --> 21:23.949
- Ugh, this is literally going
to be the worst vacation ever.

21:24.016 --> 21:27.719
This is literally
the best vacation ever.

21:27.786 --> 21:29.454
[overlapping agreements]

21:29.521 --> 21:31.690
- Why were we
so against this place?

21:31.757 --> 21:32.691
[rings cowbell]

21:32.758 --> 21:37.429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:37.496 --> 21:39.698
<i>- [blows conch shell]</i>
<i>- [rings cowbell]</i>

21:39.765 --> 21:41.533
- Ah!

21:41.600 --> 21:43.168
Ooh!
[grunts]

21:43.235 --> 21:44.036
[screams]

21:44.102 --> 21:45.337
<i>- [blows conch shell]</i>

21:45.404 --> 21:46.471
- [screams]

21:46.538 --> 21:47.472
<i>- [rings cowbell]</i>

21:47.539 --> 21:52.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:52.377 --> 21:54.579
- It may not be much
of a vacation for me,

21:54.646 --> 21:57.516
but it's worth it if all ten
of my sisters are happy.

21:57.582 --> 22:00.752
I'd say
everything turned out A-okay.

22:00.819 --> 22:02.454
[sinister laughter]

22:02.521 --> 22:03.588
[screams]

22:03.655 --> 22:05.891
The hill people
hiding in the trees!

22:10.595 --> 22:12.030
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.097 --> 22:13.899
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.965 --> 22:16.835
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.902 --> 22:19.304
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.371 --> 22:23.375
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show our</i>
<i>love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.442 --> 22:24.743
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.810 --> 22:26.344
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.411 --> 22:27.512
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.579 --> 22:28.747
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.814 --> 22:30.182
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.248 --> 22:32.718
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.784 --> 22:35.320
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.387 --> 22:36.655
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
